News from ASA From the Desk of Bill Fortier
Dear {!Contact.FirstName},
I would like to share with you some recent changes within Business Development and Strategic Lender Services here at American Student Assistance (ASA). Jeff Bentley, your previous Lender Relationship Manager, has accepted a position as a Regional Account Executive enhancing our New England Market team lead by Caroline Menendez (Business Development Manger, New England Market).
With this change, I will be your new Lender Relationship Manager. Although I will be your primary contact, I would like to take this opportunity to introduce Christa Ellis. Christa was recently promoted to Lender Relationship Manager and will be working with me to continue strengthening the relationship that Jeff has built with you over the last year. A constant through this change will be Trent Watson, your companys day-to-day operational contact, we will be working to enhance ASAs level of service and communication in order to ensure your needs are being met.
As you may know, this year the national cohort default rate rose from 4.6 to 5.2 percent. ASAs cohort default rate, however, has continued to fall. Our 2006 cohort default rate stands at 1.4 percent, the lowest among all national guarantors. We attribute this success to the growth and expansion of our Wellness programs, especially as we collaborate more closely with you, our lender partner. Our results clearly demonstrate that were making a difference in borrowers lives. I look forward to working with you and your team to ensure borrowers in our portfolio are receiving all of the benefits of an ASA guarantee.
If you are planning on having a sales meeting or team conference call in the near future, I would appreciate the opportunity to introduce myself and share our products and services with you.
I would also like to ensure you and your sales team are receiving ASA deliverables, like our quarterly Partnership Exchange newsletter. Could you please forward me an updated list and an organizational chart of your sales team so we can make sure our information is up to date? I am also attaching a list of our business development team with contact information and territories for you to share with your team.
We look forward to working with you and your teams. Please feel free to contact me with any questions or concerns you may have.
Thanks,
Bill Fortier
